Here's an example MATLAB code that demonstrates how to create an augmented reality application that overlays a 3D model of an endangered species onto a live video feed:
```
% Load the 3D model of the endangered species
speciesModel = load('speciesModel.mat');
% Create a webcam object to capture the live video feed
cam = webcam();
% Create an augmented reality object
ar = augmentedReality();
% Loop through the live video frames
while true
 % Capture a frame from the webcam
 frame = snapshot(cam);

 % Detect the marker in the frame
 marker = detectMarker(frame);

 % If a marker is detected, overlay the 3D model onto the frame
 if ~isempty(marker)
 % Get the pose of the marker
 pose = estimatePose(marker);

 % Overlay the 3D model onto the frame
 ar.Model = speciesModel;
 ar.Pose = pose;
 frame = ar.render(frame);
 end

 % Display the frame
 imshow(frame);
end
```
This code assumes that you have already created the `detectMarker` and `estimatePose` functions to detect and track the markers in the environment. It also assumes that you have loaded the 3D model of the endangered species into a MATLAB variable called `speciesModel`.
To make the augmented reality experience more interactive, you could add additional functionality to the code, such as displaying information about the species when the user clicks on it, or creating challenges or quizzes that the user must complete within the augmented reality environment.

